.TH OPENTELEMETRY-NODEJS 1 "@DATE@" "opentelemetry-nodejs-autoinstrumentation @VERSION@" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
opentelemetry-nodejs \- OpenTelemetry Node.js Auto-Instrumentation Agent
.SH DESCRIPTION
The OpenTelemetry Node.js Auto-Instrumentation Agent automatically instruments
Node.js applications to collect distributed traces, metrics, and logs.
.PP
When installed alongside
.BR opentelemetry-injector (8),
Node.js applications are automatically instrumented without code changes.
.SH CONFIGURATION
.TP
.I /etc/opentelemetry/nodejs/otel-config.yaml
Default configuration file for the Node.js agent.
.TP
.I /etc/opentelemetry/injector/conf.d/nodejs.conf
Drop-in configuration that registers the Node.js agent with the injector.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/lib/opentelemetry/nodejs/
Node.js agent installation directory.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B OTEL_SERVICE_NAME
Service name for telemetry data.
.TP
.B OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT
OTLP endpoint (default: http://localhost:4317).
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR opentelemetry-injector (8)
.PP
https://opentelemetry.io/docs/zero-code/js/
